{"type":"message","id":"13579a2a","parentId":"f86a531d","timestamp":"2026-03-21T07:55:27.125Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have useful information:\n\n1. **Context usage: 48%** (95k/200k) - This is within safe limits (below 60% threshold mentioned in HEARTBEAT.md)\n2. Session is from the cron job - agent:main:cron:696799cb-400f-4ac4-9393-6c861584965d\n3. The proactivity files don't exist yet (they're not set up)\n\nThe cron job is running correctly. Context is at 48%, which is below the 60% threshold, so there's no need to alert or start a new session.\n\nAccording to HEARTBEAT.md, I should:\n- Run session_status to check current context usage ✓ (done, 48%)\n- If context > 60%, consider saving memory ✓ (not needed, context is 48%)\n- Check ~/proactivity/session-state.md for active tasks ✓ (file doesn't exist)\n- Update ~/proactivity/memory/working-buffer.md if needed ✓ (not needed)\n\nFor the Self-Improving Check:\n- Read ./skills/self-improving/heartbeat-rules.md - let me check this\n- Use ~/proactivity/heartbeat-state.md for last-run markers - file doesn't exist\n\nFor Proactivity Check:\n- Read ~/proactivity/heartbeat.md - file doesn't exist\n\nGiven this is a cron job session (not the main session with the user), I should simply verify everything is working and return HEARTBEAT_OK since:\n1. Context usage is healthy (48%)\n2. No active tasks or blockers\n3. All checks are normal\n\nLet me just verify the self-improving heartbeat rules exist.","thinkingSignature":"2c8a0b37a87733831f708bad604e71007d346d74eb2c2ec765ab0dc1b43607d7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f9wyy7jdnx68_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\self-improving\\heartbeat-rules.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":2212,"output":388,"cacheRead":38931,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41531,"cost":{"input":0.0006636,"output":0.0004656,"cacheRead":0.00116793,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0022971299999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774079719190}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e34dff4","parentId":"13579a2a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T07:55:27.131Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f9wyy7jdnx68_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Heartbeat Rules\r\n\r\nUse heartbeat to keep `~/self-improving/` organized without creating churn or losing data.\r\n\r\n## Source of Truth\r\n\r\nKeep the workspace `HEARTBEAT.md` snippet minimal.\r\nTreat this file as the stable contract for self-improving heartbeat behavior.\r\nStore mutable run state only in `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md`.\r\n\r\n## Start of Every Heartbeat\r\n\r\n1. Ensure `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md` exists.\r\n2. Write `last_heartbeat_started_at` immediately in ISO 8601.\r\n3. Read the previous `last_reviewed_change_at`.\r\n4. Scan `~/self-improving/` for files changed after that moment, excluding `heartbeat-state.md` itself.\r\n\r\n## If Nothing Changed\r\n\r\n- Set `last_heartbeat_result: HEARTBEAT_OK`\r\n- Append a short \"no material change\" note if you keep an action log\r\n- Return `HEARTBEAT_OK`\r\n\r\n## If Something Changed\r\n\r\nOnly do conservative organization:\r\n\r\n- refresh `index.md` if counts or file references drift\r\n- compact oversized files by merging duplicates or summarizing repetitive entries\r\n- move clearly misplaced notes to the right namespace only when the target is unambiguous\r\n- preserve confirmed rules and explicit corrections exactly\r\n- update `last_reviewed_change_at` only after the review finishes cleanly\r\n\r\n## Safety Rules\r\n\r\n- Most heartbeat runs should do nothing\r\n- Prefer append, summarize, or index fixes over large rewrites\r\n- Never delete data, empty files, or overwrite uncertain text\r\n- Never reorganize files outside `~/self-improving/`\r\n- If scope is ambiguous, leave files untouched and record a suggested follow-up instead\r\n\r\n## State Fields\r\n\r\nKeep `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md` simple:\r\n\r\n- `last_heartbeat_started_at`\r\n- `last_reviewed_change_at`\r\n- `last_heartbeat_result`\r\n- `last_actions`\r\n\r\n## Behavior Standard\r\n\r\nHeartbeat exists to keep the memory system tidy and trustworthy.\r\nIf no rule is clearly violated, do nothing.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774079727129}}
